President Biden will meet with Israeli Prime Minister Naftali Bennett at the White House on August 26, 2021. The visit aims to strengthen the partnership between the United States and Israel and highlight the deep ties between the two countries. They will discuss important regional and global security matters, with a particular focus on Iran. The leaders will also address efforts to promote peace, security, and prosperity for both Israelis and Palestinians, emphasizing the importance of working towards a more peaceful and secure future for the region.